<p>This layout can now be used on each â€˜tag pageâ€™ - that is, each tag needs a page to display its contents. Use like so:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
---
layout: tagpage
title: "TagÂ pageÂ forÂ TAGNAME"
tag: TAGNAME
---

TheseÂ areÂ postsÂ thatÂ areÂ taggedÂ withÂ the **{{Â page.tagÂ }}** tag.

&lt;!--
$$Â RemoveÂ (orÂ doÂ notÂ copy)Â thisÂ andÂ everythingÂ belowÂ it.
$$Â ReplaceÂ TAGNAMEÂ withÂ theÂ nameÂ ofÂ theÂ newÂ tagÂ inÂ bothÂ placesÂ ofÂ theÂ frontmatter.Â NoÂ otherÂ changesÂ areÂ necessary.
$$Â NewÂ fileÂ nameÂ shouldÂ matchÂ theÂ tagname.md
--&gt;

</code></pre></div></div>
<p>Change the TAGNAME in both places to the tag. Each tag needs its own file, placed in a folder (in the root) named <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tag</code>. Feel free to change the content as desired.</p>

<h2 id="one-page-that-lists-all-tags-with-a-list-of-their-posts">One page that lists all tags with a list of their posts</h2>
<p>In the root folder, create a page called <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tags.html</code> with the following content:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
---
layout:Â page
title:Â SiteÂ tags
---

&lt;h1&gt;TagsÂ usedÂ onÂ thisÂ site&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;hr/&gt;
{%Â forÂ tagÂ inÂ site.tagsÂ %}
	&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="{{Â site.urlÂ }}/Blog/tag/{{Â tag[0]Â }}" style="color:#bbbbbb;"&gt;{{Â tag[0]Â }}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		{%Â forÂ postÂ inÂ tag[1]Â %}
				&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="{{Â post.urlÂ |Â prepend:site.baseurlÂ }}"&gt;{{Â post.titleÂ }}
			&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		{%Â endforÂ %}
	&lt;/ul&gt;
{%Â endforÂ %}

</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="create-a-list-of-all-tags-on-the-site">Create a list of all tags on the site</h2>
<p>Create a list of tags used on the site (without the list of associated posts). Each tag will link to its tag page.</p>

<p>Add a file to the _includes folder called <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tagArchive.html</code> with the following:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>
&lt;h2\&gt;Archive&lt;/h2\&gt;
{%Â captureÂ temptagsÂ %}
	{%Â forÂ tagÂ inÂ site.tagsÂ %}
		{{Â tag\[1\].sizeÂ |Â plus:Â 1000Â }}#{{Â tag\[0\]Â }}#{{Â tag\[1\].sizeÂ }}
	{%Â endforÂ %}
{%Â endcaptureÂ %}
{%Â assignÂ sortedtemptagsÂ =Â temptagsÂ |Â split:'Â 'Â |Â sortÂ |Â reverseÂ %}
{%Â forÂ temptagÂ inÂ sortedtemptagsÂ %}
	{%Â assignÂ tagitemsÂ =Â temptagÂ |Â split:Â '#'Â %}
	{%Â captureÂ tagnameÂ %}{{Â tagitems\[1\]Â }}{%Â endcaptureÂ %}
	&lt;a href\="{{Â siteurlÂ |Â prepend:site.baseurlÂ }}/tag/{{Â tagnameÂ }}" class\="postTags"\&gt;&lt;nobr\&gt;{{Â tagnameÂ }}&lt;/nobr\&gt;&lt;/a\&gt;&amp;nbsp;
{%Â endforÂ %}

</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Place it in a page or post^[I put this at the top or bottom of my tags.html page from the previous section]</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{%Â includeÂ tagArchive.htmlÂ %}</code></p>
